    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fossiliferous limestone composed almost entirely of the fossil skeletal parts of crinoids, marine invertebrates of the phylum Echinodermata; crinoidal limestone is particularly plentiful in North America.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Caliza fosilífera compuesta casi enteramente de las partes esqueléticas fósiles de crinoides, invertebrados marinos del filum Echinodermata; la caliza crinoidal es particularmente abundante en América del Norte.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fossielhoudende kalksteen die vrijwel geheel bestaat uit de fossiele skeletdelen van crinoïden, ongewervelde zeedieren uit de stam van de Echinodermata. Crinoïde kalksteen komt vooral in Noord-Amerika veel voor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種化石石灰岩，幾乎完全由海百合的化石骨骼部分所構成。海百合為棘皮動物門（phylum Echinodermata）的海生無脊椎動物。海百合石灰岩特別盛產於北美洲。 </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
